Let $omegafinal=1+boredone\,immutable+boredtwo\,immutable^{2}+\cdots$ be a formal power series with coefficients in the field of two elements. Let
\[
boredvar =
\begin{cases}
1 & \parbox{2in}{if every block of zeros in the binary expansion of $constantval$ has an even number of zeros in the block} \\[.3in]
0 & \text{otherwise.}
\end{cases}
\]
(For example, $boredthirtysix=1$ because $36=100100_2$ and $boredtwenty=0$ because $20=10100_2.$)
Prove that $omegafinal^{3}+immutable\,omegafinal+1=0.$
